def: The state or quality of being null and void; invalidity;forfeiture. Burrill.
A kind of small black perch.
Master; sir; -- a title of respect formerly applied to a knightor a clergyman, and sometimes to the lord of a manor. Cowell.
Any animal which is unusually small, as compared with others ofits kind; -- applied particulary to domestic animals.
Shaped or sounding like a trumpet; trumpetlike.
Turned round, as a wheel; also, wheel-shaped; rotate.
